### **Anti-Pattern 4: Using `synchronize: true` in Tests**

**The Problem**: While convenient, `synchronize: true` can lead to tests that pass locally but fail in CI due to schema drift. It‚Äôs also not how your production app runs.

**‚ùå Bad Code**:

```ts
TypeOrmModule.forRoot({
  // ...
  synchronize: true, // ‚ùå Avoid in all environments, including tests
})
```

**‚úÖ Correct Approach (Use Migrations)**:

```ts
// In your integration test setup
TypeOrmModule.forRoot({
  // ...
  migrations: [path.join(__dirname, '../migrations/*{.ts,.js}')],
  migrationsRun: true, // Run migrations to set up the test DB schema
})
```

> **Best Practice**: "Use Migrations: Avoid relying on synchronize: true in production" ‚Äî this applies to test environments as well for consistency .

